data.title: Iowa Energy head coach fired; Cyprien named interim coach
authors: Register staff report, The Des Moines Register
data.meta_description: Glynn Cyprien, a native of New Orleans, was named interim head coach.
data.text:
DES MOINES, Ia. — Iowa Energy head coach Matt Woodley was relieved of his head coaching duties, effective immediately, on Monday.

Glynn Cyprien, a native of New Orleans, was named interim head coach.

Cyprien joined the Memphis Grizzlies in the 2014-15 season as basketball operations assistant/scout, where he coached or recruited current and former NBA players including Tony Allen, Khris Middleton, Patrick Patterson, Patrick Beverley, Jodie Meeks, Will Barton, Sonny Weems, Josh Harrellson, John Lucas III and Shawn Marion.

Before returning to Memphis, Cyprien served three seasons (2011-14) as associate head coach at Texas A&M. His resume also includes assistant coaching stints at Kentucky (2007-09), Arkansas (2006-07), New Mexico State (2005-06), Oklahoma State (2000-04), UNLV (1995-2000), Western Kentucky (1994-95), Jacksonville (1991-94), Lamar (1990-91) and UTSA (1987-90).

The New Orleans native lettered two seasons as a player at Southern University-New Orleans and earned his bachelor’s degree in physical education from UTSA in 2004.

The Energy travel to Frisco, Texas, on Wednesday to take on the Texas Legends.
